0%26quot%3BAnd%20we%20were%20able%20to%20do%20that%20over%20the%20course%20of%20this%20year%20because%20the%20labor%20market%20was%20in%20very%20solid%20condition%2C%20with%20strong%20job%20creation%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjerome-powell-jackson-hole-speech-fed-interest-rate-cut-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESeptember%20meeting%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20can%20no%20longer%20say%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225491543d-bdbf-4ae0-8874-7b7c6479edcc%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Fed%20is%20missing%20a%20key%20piece%20of%20economic%20data%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20the%20latest%20jobs%20report%2C%20Fed%20leaders%20will%20have%20to%20rely%20on%20other%20economic%20indicators%20to%20make%20their%20rate%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInflation%20data%20is%20crucial%20for%20one%20side%20of%20the%20Fed's%20dual%20mandate.%20The%20consumer%20price%20index%2C%20one%20measure%20of%20inflation%2C%20rose%20slightly%20below%20the%203.1%25%20forecast%20in%20September%2C%20hitting%203%25%20for%20the%20first%20time%20since%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStephen%20Kates%2C%20a%20financial%20analyst%20at%20Bankrate%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20he%20expected%20the%20Fed%20to%20make%20a%20rate%20cut%20regardless%20of%20the%20new%20inflation%20data%2C%20but%20feels%20that%20cooler-than-expected%20rate%20cemented%20the%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20if%20we%20got%20slightly%20higher%20inflation%2C%20even%20if%20inflation%20could%20come%20in%20exactly%20at%20expectations%2C%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20had%20made%20it%20relatively%20clear%20that%20they%20were%20more%20comfortable%20with%20the%20level%20of%20inflation%20that%20we've%20had%20relative%20to%20now%20the%20deterioration%20in%20the%20labor%20market%2C%26quot%3B%20Kates%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPre-shutdown%20patterns%20in%20the%20job%20market%20also%20make%20a%20strong%20case%20for%20a%20rate%20reduction.%20Openings%20have%20declined%2C%20and%20unemployment%20has%20been%20creeping%20up%2C%20meaning%20the%20market%20isn't%20keeping%20up%20with%20the%20number%20of%20Americans%20looking%20for%20work.%20The%20central%20bank%20might%20not%20have%20the%20latest%20data%2C%20but%20Powell%20said%20last%20month%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20marked%20slowing%20in%20both%20the%20supply%20of%20and%20demand%20for%20workers%20is%20unusual%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20called%20for%20a%20less%20restrictive%20policy%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed%20may%20also%20lean%20on%20soft%20economic%20indicators%20to%20make%20its%20decision.%20A%20key%20marker%20of%20consumer%20sentiment%2C%20for%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sca.isr.umich.edu%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edipped%20in%20October%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20suggests%20that%20Americans%20are%20feeling%20the%20heat%20of%20high%20prices%20and%20limited%20job%20opportunities%2C%20meaning%20they're%20less%20likely%20to%20spend%20money.%20Another%20rate%20cut%20could%20help%20stimulate%20a%20seemingly%20sluggish%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20all%20Fed%20leaders%20agree%20on%20how%20much%20the%20bank%20should%20cut%20rates.%20A%20few%20committee%20members%20dissented%20from%20Powell's%20restrictive%20policy%20patterns%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffed-dot-plot-one-member-wants-bigger-interest-rate-cuts-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eone%20member%20called%20for%20a%201.25%25%20rate%20reduction%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%20last%20month%20%E2%80%94%20far%20more%20than%20any%20other%20voting%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%20has%20also%20been%20vocal%20about%20his%20desire%20for%20more%20rate%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20really%20believe%20that%20Jerome%20'Too%20Late'%20Powell%20is%20an%20OBSTRUCTIONIST!%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftruthsocial.